The Criticality Diagnostics IE is sent

contains information about which IEs were not comprehended or were missing.

definitionList.name: Allocation and Retention Priority

This IE specifies the relative importance
of a QoS flow compared to other QoS flows for allocation and retention of
NG-RAN resources.

elementList.name: Priority Level
elementList.description: Desc.: This IE defines the relative importance of a resource request (see TS 23.501 [9]). Usage: Values are ordered in decreasing order of priority, i.e., with 1 as the highest priority and 15 as the lowest priority.

elementList.name: Pre-emption Capability
elementList.type: ENUMERATED (shall not trigger pre-emption, may trigger pre-emption, )
elementList.description: Desc.: This IE indicates the pre-emption capability of the request on other QoS flows (see TS 23.501 [9]). Usage: The QoS flow shall not pre-empt other QoS flows or, the QoS flow may pre-empt other QoS flows. Note: The Pre-emption Capability indicator applies to the allocation of resources for a QoS flow and as such it provides the trigger to the pre-emption procedures/processes of the NG-RAN node.

elementList.name: Pre-emption Vulnerability
elementList.description: Desc.: This IE indicates the vulnerability of the QoS flow to pre-emption of other QoS flows (see TS 23.501 [9]). Usage: The QoS flow shall not be pre-empted by other QoS flows or the QoS flow may be pre-empted by other QoS flows. Note: The Pre-emption Vulnerability indicator applies for the entire duration of the QoS flow, unless modified and as such indicates whether the QoS flow is a target of the pre-emption procedures/processes of the NG-RAN node.

definitionList.name: Source to Target Transparent Container

related information from the handover source to the handover target through the
core network; it is produced by
the source RAN node and is transmitted
to the target RAN node.

elementList.name: Source to Target Transparent Container
elementList.description: This IE includes a transparent container from the source RAN node to the target RAN node. The octets of the OCTET STRING are encoded according to the specifications of the target system. Note: In the current version of the specification, this IE may carry either the Source NG-RAN Node to Target NG-RAN Node Transparent Container IE or the Source eNB to Target eNB Transparent Container IE as defined in TS 36.413 [16] or the Source RNC to Target RNC Transparent Container IE as defined in TS 25.413 [28].

related information from the handover target to the handover source through the
core network; it is produced by
the target RAN node and is transmitted
to the source RAN node.

elementList.name: Target to Source Transparent Container
elementList.description: This IE includes a transparent container from the target RAN node to the source RAN node. The octets of the OCTET STRING are encoded according to the specifications of the target system. Note: In the current version of the specification, this IE may carry either the Target NG-RAN Node to Source NG-RAN Node Transparent Container IE or the Target eNB to Source eNB Transparent Container IE as defined in TS 36.413 [16], or the Target RNC to Source RNC Transparent Container IE as defined in TS 25.413 [28].

definitionList.name: Emergency Fallback Indicator
descriptionList: The IE indicates emergency service fallback.

definitionList.name: Security Indication
descriptionList:
This IE contains the user plane integrity protection
indication and confidentiality protection indication which indicates the requirements
on UP integrity protection and ciphering for corresponding PDU sessions, respectively.
Additionally, this IE contains the maximum integrity protected data rate per UE
for integrity protection for DRBs.

elementList.name: Integrity Protection Indication
elementList.description: Indicates whether UP integrity protection shall apply, should apply or shall not apply for the concerned PDU session.

elementList.name: Confidentiality Protection Indication
elementList.description: Indicates whether UP ciphering shall apply, should apply or shall not apply for the concerned PDU session.

elementList.name: Maximum Integrity Protected Data Rate Uplink
elementList.description: Indicates the maximum aggregate rate for integrity protected DRBs supported by the UE in UL. If the Maximum Integrity Protected Data Rate Downlink IE is absent, this IE applies to both UL and DL.

elementList.name: Maximum Integrity Protected Data Rate Downlink
elementList.description: Indicates the maximum aggregate rate for integrity protected DRBs supported by the UE in the DL.

conditionList.explanation:
This IE shall be present if the Integrity
  Protection Indication IE within the Security Indication
  IE is set to  required  or  preferred .

definitionList.name: Non Dynamic 5QI Descriptor
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the QoS Characteristics
for a standardized or pre-configured 5QI for downlink and uplink.

elementList.name: 5QI
elementList.description: Indicates the standardized or pre-configured 5QI as specified in TS 23.501 [9].

elementList.name: Priority Level
elementList.description: Priority Level is specified in TS 23.501 [9]. When included, it overrides standardized or pre-configured value.

elementList.name: Averaging Window
elementList.description: Averaging Window is specified in TS 23.501 [9]. When included, it overrides standardized or pre-configured value.

elementList.name: Maximum Data Burst Volume
elementList.description: Maximum Data Burst Volume is specified in TS 23.501 [9]. When included, it overrides standardized or pre-configured value.

elementList.name: CN Packet Delay Budget Downlink
elementList.description: Core Network Packet Delay Budget is specified in TS 23.501 [9]. This IE may be present in case of GBR QoS flows and is ignored otherwise.

elementList.name: CN Packet Delay Budget Uplink
elementList.description: Core Network Packet Delay Budget is specified in TS 23.501 [9]. This IE may be present in case of GBR QoS flows and is ignored otherwise.

definitionList.name: Source NG-RAN Node to Target NG-RAN Node Transparent Container
descriptionList:
This IE is produced by the source NG-RAN node and is transmitted to the
target NG-RAN node. For inter-system
handovers to 5G, the IE is transmitted from the external handover source to the
target NG-RAN node.
This IE is transparent to the 5GC.

elementList.name: RRC Container
elementList.description: Includes the RRC HandoverPreparationInformation message as defined in TS 38.331 [18] if the target is a gNB. Includes the RRC HandoverPreparationInformation message as defined in TS 36.331 [21] if the target is an ng-eNB.

elementList.name: PDU Session Resource Information List
elementList.description: For intra-system handovers in NG-RAN.

elementList.name: DRBs to QoS Flows Mapping List
E-RAB Information List
elementList.description: For inter-system handovers to 5G.

elementList.name: SgNB UE X2AP ID
elementList.description: Allocated at the Source en-gNB

rangeBoundList.explanation:
Maximum no. of PDU sessions allowed towards one
  UE. Value is 256.

Maximum no. of QoS flows allowed within one
  PDU session. Value is 64.

Maximum no. of E-RABs allowed towards one UE. Value
  is 256.

definitionList.name: Target NG-RAN Node to Source NG-RAN Node Transparent Container
descriptionList:
This IE is produced by the target NG-RAN node and is transmitted to the
source NG-RAN node. For inter-system handovers to 5G, the IE is transmitted
from the target NG-RAN node to the external relocation source.
This IE is transparent to the 5GC.

elementList.name: RRC Container
elementList.description: Includes the RRC HandoverCommand message as defined in TS 38.331 [18] if the target is a gNB. Includes the RRC HandoverCommand message as defined in TS 36.331 [21] if the target is an ng-eNB.

elementList.name: DAPS Response Information
elementList.description: Indicates the response to a requested DAPS Handover

rangeBoundList.explanation:
Maximum no. of DRBs allowed towards one UE.
  Value is 32.

definitionList.name: Allowed NSSAI
descriptionList: This IE contains the allowed NSSAI.

rangeBoundList.explanation: Maximum no. of allowed S-NSSAI. Value is 8.

definitionList.name: Relative AMF Capacity
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the relative processing capacity
of an AMF with respect to the other AMFs in the AMF Set in order to load-balance
AMFs within an AMF Set defined in TS 23.501 [9].

definitionList.name: DL Forwarding
descriptionList:
This IE indicates that the QoS flow or E-RAB is proposed for forwarding
of downlink packets.

definitionList.name: DRBs to QoS Flows Mapping List
descriptionList:
This IE contains a list of DRBs containing
information about the mapped QoS flows.

elementList.name: DRBs to QoS Flows Mapping Item
Associated QoS Flow List
elementList.description: Contains information of the QoS flows mapped to the DRB

rangeBoundList.explanation:
Maximum no. of DRBs allowed towards one UE. Value
  is 32.

definitionList.name: Message Identifier
descriptionList:
This IE identifies the warning message. It
is set by the AMF and transferred to the UE by the NG-RAN node.

elementList.name: Message Identifier
elementList.description: This IE is set by the 5GC, transferred to the UE by the NG-RAN node.

definitionList.name: Serial Number
descriptionList:
This IE identifies a particular message from
the source and type indicated by the Message Identifier and is altered every
time the message with a given Message Identifier is changed.

definitionList.name: Warning Area List
descriptionList:
This IE indicates
the areas where the warning message needs to be broadcast or cancelled.

rangeBoundList.explanation:
Maximum no. of Cell ID subject for warning message
  broadcast. Value is 65535.

Maximum no. of TAI subject for warning message
  broadcast. Value is 65535.

Maximum no. of Emergency Area ID subject for warning
  message broadcast. Value is 65535.

definitionList.name: Number of Broadcasts Requested
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the
number of times a message is to be broadcast.

definitionList.name: Warning Type
descriptionList:
This IE indicates
types of the disaster. This IE also indicates that a Primary Notification is included.
This IE can be used by the UE to differentiate the type of alert according to the
type of disaster.

definitionList.name: Data Coding Scheme
descriptionList:
This IE identifies
the alphabet or coding employed for the message characters and message handling
at the UE (it is passed transparently from the 5GC to the UE).

definitionList.name: Warning Message Contents
descriptionList:
This IE contains user information, e.g., the message with warning contents,
and will be broadcast over the radio interface.

definitionList.name: Broadcast Completed Area List
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the
areas where either resources are available to perform the broadcast or where
broadcast is performed successfully.

elementList.name: Completed Cell in Emergency Area ID List
Completed Cell in Emergency Area ID List

rangeBoundList.explanation:
Maximum no. of Cell ID subject for warning
  message broadcast. Value is 65535.

Maximum no. of TAI subject for warning message
  broadcast. Value is 65535.

Maximum no. of Emergency Area ID subject for warning
  message broadcast. Value is 65535.
Maximum no. of Cell ID within a TAI. Value is 65535.

Maximum no. of Cell ID within an Emergency Area.
  Value is 65535.

definitionList.name: Broadcast Cancelled Area List
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the areas where broadcast
was stopped successfully.

elementList.name: Cancelled Cell in Emergency Area ID List
Cancelled Cell in Emergency Area ID List

rangeBoundList.explanation:
Maximum no. of Cell ID subject for warning message
  broadcast. Value is 65535.

Maximum no. of TAI subject for warning message broadcast.
  Value is 65535.

Maximum no. of Emergency Area ID subject for warning
  message broadcast. Value is 65535.

Maximum no. of Cell ID within a TAI. Value is
  65535.

Maximum no. of Cell ID within an Emergency Area.
  Value is 65535.

definitionList.name: Number of Broadcasts
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the number of times
that a particular message has been broadcast in a given warning area.

elementList.name: Number of Broadcasts
elementList.description: This IE is set to '0' if valid results are not known or not available. It is set to 65535 if the counter results have overflowed.

definitionList.name: Concurrent Warning Message Indicator
descriptionList:
This IE indicates to the NG-RAN node that
the received warning message is a new message to be scheduled for concurrent broadcast
with any other ongoing broadcast of warning messages.

elementList.name: Concurrent Warning Message Indicator
elementList.description: This IE is used to identify a PWS type warning system which allows the broadcast of multiple concurrent warning messages over the radio.

definitionList.name: Cancel-All Warning Messages Indicator
descriptionList:
This IE indicates to the NG-RAN node to stop
all already ongoing broadcast of warning messages in the NG-RAN node or in an area.

definitionList.name: Emergency Area ID
descriptionList:
This IE is used to indicate
the area which has the emergency impact.

elementList.name: Emergency Area ID
elementList.description: Emergency Area ID may consist of several cells. Emergency Area ID is defined by the operator.

definitionList.name: Repetition Period
descriptionList:
This IE indicates
the periodicity of the warning message to be broadcast.

elementList.name: Repetition Period
elementList.description: The unit of value 1 to 217-1 is [second].

definitionList.name: PDU Session ID
descriptionList:
This IE identifies a PDU Session for a UE.
The definition and use of the PDU Session ID is specified in TS 23.501 [9].

definitionList.name: QoS Flow Identifier
descriptionList:
This IE identifies a QoS flow within a PDU
Session. The definition and use of the QoS Flow Identifier is specified in TS 23.501 [9].

definitionList.name: PDU Session Type
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the PDU Session Type as
specified in TS 23.501 [9].

definitionList.name: DRB ID
descriptionList: This IE contains the DRB ID.

definitionList.name: Masked IMEISV
descriptionList: This IE contains the IMEISV value with a mask, to identify a terminal model without identifying an individual Mobile Equipment.

elementList.name: Masked IMEISV
elementList.description: Coded as the International Mobile station Equipment Identity and Software Version Number (IMEISV) defined in TS 23.003 [23] with the last 4 digits of the SNR masked by setting the corresponding bits to 1. The first to fourth bits correspond to the first digit of the IMEISV, the fifth to eighth bits correspond to the second digit of the IMEISV, and so on.

definitionList.name: New Security Context Indicator
descriptionList:
This IE indicates that the AMF has activated
a new 5G NAS security context as described in TS 33.501 [13].

elementList.name: New Security Context Indicator
elementList.description: The NSCI as defined in TS 33.501 [13].

definitionList.name: Time to Wait
descriptionList:
This IE defines
the minimum allowed waiting time.

definitionList.name: Global N3IWF ID
descriptionList:
This IE is used
to globally identify an N3IWF.

definitionList.name: UE Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate
descriptionList:
This IE is applicable for all Non-GBR QoS flows
per UE which is defined for the downlink and the uplink direction and a subscription
parameter provided by the AMF to the NG-RAN node.

elementList.name: UE Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate
elementList.description: Applicable for Non-GBR QoS flows.

elementList.name: UE Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate Downlink
elementList.description: This IE indicates the UE Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate as specified in TS 23.501 [9] in the downlink direction.

elementList.name: UE Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate Uplink
elementList.description: This IE indicates the UE Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate as specified in TS 23.501 [9] in the uplink direction.

definitionList.name: Security Result
descriptionList:
This IE indicates whether the security policy
indicated as "preferred" in the Security Indication IE is performed
or not.

elementList.name: Integrity Protection Result
elementList.description: Indicates whether UP integrity protection is performed or not for the concerned PDU session.

elementList.name: Confidentiality Protection Result
elementList.description: Indicates whether UP ciphering is performed or not for the concerned PDU session.

definitionList.name: User Plane Security Information
descriptionList:
This IE indicates user plane security information
related to security policy.

definitionList.name: Index to RAT/Frequency Selection Priority
descriptionList:
This IE is used
to define local configuration for RRM strategies such as camp priorities in Idle
mode and control of inter-RAT/inter-frequency handover in Active mode (see TS
23.501 [9]).

definitionList.name: Data Forwarding Accepted
descriptionList:
This IE indicates
that the NG-RAN node accepts the
proposed DL data forwarding for the QoS flow which is subject
to data forwarding.

definitionList.name: Data Forwarding Not Possible
descriptionList:
This IE indicates that the 5GC decided that the corresponding PDU session will not
be subject to data forwarding.

definitionList.name: Direct Forwarding Path Availability
descriptionList:
This IE indicates whether a direct forwarding
path is available.

definitionList.name: Location Reporting Request Type
descriptionList: This IE indicates the type of location request to be handled by the NG-RAN node.

elementList.name: Event Type
elementList.type: ENUMERATED (direct, change of serving cell, UE presence in the area of interest, stop change of serving cell, stop UE presence in the area of interest, cancel location reporting for the UE, )

elementList.name: Location Reporting Reference ID to be Cancelled

rangeBoundList.explanation: Maximum no. of areas of interest. Value is 64.

conditionList.explanation:
This IE shall be
  present if the Event Type IE is set to "stop UE presence in the
  area of interest".

definitionList.name: Area of Interest
descriptionList:
This IE
indicates the area of interest.

elementList.name: Area of Interest RAN Node List
Area of Interest RAN Node Item

rangeBoundList.explanation:
Maximum no. of tracking areas in an area of
  interest. Value is 16.

Maximum no. of cells in an area of interest. Value
  is 256.

Maximum no. of NG-RAN nodes in an area of
  interest. Value is 64.

definitionList.name: UE Presence in Area of Interest List
descriptionList:
This IE indicates
the UE presence in the area of interest.

elementList.name: UE Presence in Area of Interest Item

rangeBoundList.explanation: Maximum no. of areas of interest. Value is 64.

definitionList.name: UE Radio Capability for Paging
descriptionList:
This IE contains
paging specific UE Radio Capability information.

elementList.name: UE Radio Capability for Paging of NR
elementList.description: Includes the RRC UERadioPagingInformation message as defined in TS 38.331 [18].

elementList.name: UE Radio Capability for Paging of E-UTRA
elementList.description: Includes the RRC UERadioPagingInformation message as defined in TS 36.331 [21].

elementList.name: UE Radio Capability for Paging of NB-IoT
elementList.description: Includes the RRC UERadioPagingInformation-NB message as defined in TS 36.331 [21].

definitionList.name: Assistance Data for Paging
descriptionList: This IE provides assistance information for paging optimisation.

elementList.name: Paging Assistance Data for CE Capable UE

definitionList.name: Assistance Data for Recommended Cells
descriptionList: This IE provides assistance information for paging in recommended cells.

definitionList.name: Recommended Cells for Paging
descriptionList:
This IE
contains the recommended cells for paging.
This IE is transparent to the 5GC.

elementList.name: Recommended Cell Item
elementList.description: Includes visited and non-visited cells, where visited cells are listed in the order the UE visited them with the most recent cell being the first in the list. Non-visited cells are included immediately after the visited cell they are associated with.

elementList.name: Time Stayed in Cell
elementList.description: This is included for visited cells and indicates the time a UE stayed in a cell in seconds. If the UE stays in a cell more than 4095 seconds, this IE is set to 4095.

rangeBoundList.explanation: Maximum no. of recommended Cells. Value is 16.

definitionList.name: Paging Attempt Information
descriptionList:
This IE includes information related to the
paging count over NG.

elementList.name: Paging Attempt Count
elementList.description: Paging attempt count (see TS 38.300 [8]).

elementList.name: Intended Number of Paging Attempts
elementList.description: Intended number of paging attempts (see TS 38.300 [8]).

elementList.name: Next Paging Area Scope
elementList.description: Indicates whether the paging area scope will change or not at next paging attempt. Usage specified in TS 38.300 [8].

definitionList.name: NG-RAN CGI
descriptionList:
This IE is used to globally identify a cell
in NG-RAN.

definitionList.name: UE Radio Capability
descriptionList: This IE contains UE Radio Capability information.

elementList.name: UE Radio Capability
elementList.description: Includes either the RRC UERadioAccessCapabilityInformation message as defined in TS 38.331 [18], or the UERadioAccessCapabilityInformation-NB message as defined in 10.6.2 of TS 36.331 [21].

definitionList.name: UE Radio Capability E-UTRA Format
descriptionList:
This IE contains UE Radio Capability
information encoded as specified in TS 36.331 [21] in order to support Mode of
operation A as specified in TS 23.501 [9].

elementList.name: UE Radio Capability E-UTRA Format
elementList.description: Includes the RRC UERadioAccessCapabilityInformation message as defined in TS 36.331 [21].

definitionList.name: Time Stamp
descriptionList: This IE contains UTC time information.

elementList.name: Time Stamp
elementList.description: Encoded in the same format as the first four octets of the 64-bit timestamp format as defined in section 6 of IETF RFC 5905 [25].

definitionList.name: Location Reporting Reference ID
descriptionList:
This IE contains the Location Reporting Reference
ID.

definitionList.name: Data Forwarding Response DRB List
descriptionList:
This IE
indicates data forwarding related information.

rangeBoundList.explanation:
Maximum no. of DRBs allowed towards one UE. Value
  is 32.

definitionList.name: Paging Priority
descriptionList:
This element indicates the paging priority
for paging a UE.

elementList.name: Paging Priority
elementList.type: ENUMERATED (PrioLevel1, PrioLevel2, PrioLevel3, PrioLevel4, PrioLevel5, PrioLevel6, PrioLevel7, PrioLevel8, )
elementList.description: Lower value codepoint indicates higher priority.

definitionList.name: Packet Loss Rate
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the Packet Loss Rate for a QoS
flow.

elementList.name: Packet Loss Rate
elementList.description: Ratio of lost packets per number of packets sent, expressed in tenth of percent.

definitionList.name: Packet Delay Budget
descriptionList: This IE indicates the Packet Delay Budget for a QoS flow.

elementList.name: Packet Delay Budget
elementList.description: Upper bound value for the delay that a packet may experience expressed in unit of 0.5ms.

definitionList.name: Packet Error Rate
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the Packet Error Rate for
a QoS flow.

elementList.name: Scalar
elementList.description: The packet error rate is expressed as Scalar x 10-k where k is the Exponent.

definitionList.name: Averaging Window
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the Averaging Window for
a QoS flow, and applies to GBR QoS flows only.

elementList.name: Averaging Window
elementList.description: Unit: ms. The default value of the IE is 2000ms.

definitionList.name: Maximum Data Burst Volume
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the Maximum Data Burst
Volume for a QoS flow, and applies to delay critical GBR QoS flows only.

elementList.name: Maximum Data Burst Volume
elementList.description: Unit: byte.

definitionList.name: Priority Level
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the Priority Level for a
QoS flow.

elementList.name: Priority Level
elementList.description: Values ordered in decreasing order of priority, i.e. with 1 as the highest priority and 127 as the lowest priority.

definitionList.name: Mobility Restriction List
descriptionList:
This IE defines roaming or access restrictions
for subsequent mobility action for which the NG-RAN provides information about
the target of the mobility action towards the UE, e.g., handover, or for SCG selection
during dual connectivity operation or for assigning proper RNAs. NG-RAN behaviour
upon receiving this IE is specified in TS 23.501 [9].

elementList.name: Equivalent PLMNs
elementList.description: Allowed PLMNs in addition to Serving PLMN. This list corresponds to the list of "equivalent PLMNs" as defined in TS 24.501 [26]. This list is part of the roaming restriction information. Roaming restrictions apply to PLMNs other than the Serving PLMN and Equivalent PLMNs.

elementList.name: RAT Restrictions
elementList.description: This IE contains RAT restriction related information as specified in TS 23.501 [9].

elementList.name: RAT Restriction Information
elementList.description: Each position in the bitmap represents a RAT. If a bit is set to "1", the respective RAT is restricted for the UE. If a bit is set to "0", the respective RAT is not restricted for the UE. Bits 3-7 reserved for future use.

elementList.name: Extended RAT Restriction Information
elementList.description: If this IE is included, the RAT Restriction Information IE is ignored.

elementList.name: Forbidden Area Information
elementList.description: This IE contains Forbidden Area information as specified in TS 23.501 [9].

elementList.name: TAC
elementList.description: The TAC of the forbidden TAI.

elementList.name: Service Area Information
elementList.description: This IE contains Service Area Restriction information as specified in TS 23.501 [9].

elementList.name: TAC
elementList.description: The TAC of the allowed TAI.

elementList.name: TAC
elementList.description: The TAC of the not-allowed TAI.

elementList.name: Last E-UTRAN PLMN Identity
elementList.description: Indicates the E-UTRAN PLMN ID from where the UE formerly handed over to 5GS and which is preferred in case of subsequent mobility to EPS.

elementList.name: Core Network Type Restriction for Serving PLMN
elementList.description: Indicates whether the UE is restricted to connect to EPC for the Serving PLMN as specified in TS 23.501 [9].

elementList.name: Core Network Type Restriction for Equivalent PLMNs
PLMN Identity
elementList.description: Includes any of the Equivalent PLMNs listed in the Mobility Restriction List IE for which CN Type restriction applies as specified in TS 23.501 [9].

elementList.name: Core Network Type Restriction
elementList.description: Indicates whether the UE is restricted to connect to EPC or to 5GC for this PLMN.

rangeBoundList.explanation: Maximum no. of equivalent PLMNs. Value is 15.
Maximum no. of allowed PLMNs. Value is 16.

Maximum no. of forbidden Tracking Area Codes. Value
  is 4096.

Maximum no. of allowed or not allowed Tracking
  Areas. Value is 16.

definitionList.name: UE Security Capabilities
descriptionList:
This IE defines the supported algorithms
for encryption and integrity protection in the UE.

elementList.name: NR Encryption Algorithms
elementList.description: Each position in the bitmap represents an encryption algorithm: "all bits equal to 0" UE supports no other algorithm than NEA0, "first bit" 128-NEA1, "second bit" 128-NEA2, "third bit" 128-NEA3, other bits reserved for future use. Value '1' indicates support and value '0' indicates no support of the algorithm. Algorithms are defined in TS 33.501 [13].

elementList.name: NR Integrity Protection Algorithms
elementList.description: Each position in the bitmap represents an integrity protection algorithm: "all bits equal to 0" UE supports no other algorithm than NIA0, "first bit" 128-NIA1, "second bit" 128-NIA2, "third bit" 128-NIA3, other bits reserved for future use. Value '1' indicates support and value '0' indicates no support of the algorithm. Algorithms are defined in TS 33.501 [13].

elementList.name: E-UTRA Encryption Algorithms
elementList.description: Each position in the bitmap represents an encryption algorithm: "all bits equal to 0" UE supports no other algorithm than EEA0, "first bit" 128-EEA1, "second bit" 128-EEA2, "third bit" 128-EEA3, other bits reserved for future use. Value '1' indicates support and value '0' indicates no support of the algorithm. Algorithms are defined in TS 33.401 [27].

elementList.name: E-UTRA Integrity Protection Algorithms
elementList.description: Each position in the bitmap represents an encryption algorithm: "all bits equal to 0" UE supports no other algorithm than EIA0, "first bit" 128-EIA1, "second bit" 128-EIA2, "third bit" 128-EIA3, other bits reserved for future use. Value '1' indicates support and value '0' indicates no support of the algorithm. Algorithms are defined in TS 33.401 [27].

definitionList.name: Security Key
descriptionList:
This IE is used to apply security in the
NG-RAN for different scenarios as defined in TS 33.501 [13].

elementList.name: Security Key
elementList.description: Key material for NG-RAN node or Next Hop Key as defined in TS 33.501 [13]

definitionList.name: Security Context
descriptionList:
This IE provides security related parameters
to the NG-RAN node which are used to derive security keys for user plane traffic
and RRC signalling messages and for security parameter generation for subsequent
mobility, see TS 33.501 [13].

elementList.name: Next Hop Chaining Count
elementList.description: Next Hop Chaining Counter (NCC) defined in TS 33.501 [13].

elementList.name: Next-Hop NH
elementList.description: The NH together with the NCC is used to derive the security configuration as defined in TS 33.501 [13].

definitionList.name: IMS Voice Support Indicator
descriptionList:
This IE is set by the NG-RAN node to indicate
whether the UE radio capabilities are compatible with the network configuration
for IMS voice.

definitionList.name: Paging DRX
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the Paging DRX as defined
in TS 38.304 [12] and TS 36.304 [29].

definitionList.name: RRC Inactive Transition Report Request
descriptionList:
This IE is used to
request the NG-RAN node to report or stop reporting to the 5GC when the UE
enters or leaves RRC_INACTIVE state.

elementList.name: RRC Inactive Transition Report Request
elementList.type: ENUMERATED (Subsequent state transition report, Single RRC connected state report, Cancel report, )

definitionList.name: RRC State
descriptionList: This IE indicates the RRC state of the UE.

elementList.name: RRC State
elementList.description: Indicates the current RRC state of the UE.

definitionList.name: Expected UE Behaviour
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the behaviour of a UE with
predictable activity and/or mobility behaviour, to assist the NG-RAN node in e.g.
determining the optimum RRC connection time or helping
with the RRC_INACTIVE state transition and RNA configuration (e.g. size and
shape of the RNA).

elementList.name: Expected HO Interval
elementList.type: ENUMERATED (sec15, sec30, sec60, sec90, sec120, sec180, long-time, )
elementList.description: Indicates the expected time interval between inter NG-RAN node handovers. If "long-time" is included, the interval between inter NG-RAN node handovers is expected to be longer than 180 seconds.

elementList.name: Expected UE Mobility
elementList.description: Indicates whether the UE is expected to be stationary or mobile.

elementList.name: Expected UE Moving Trajectory
elementList.description: Indicates the UE's expected geographical movement.

elementList.name: Expected UE Moving Trajectory Item
elementList.description: Includes list of visited and non-visited cells, where visited cells are listed in the order the UE visited them with the most recent cell being the first in the list. Non-visited cells are included immediately after the visited cell they are associated with.

elementList.name: Time Stayed in Cell
elementList.description: Included for visited cells and indicates the time a UE stayed in a cell in seconds. If the UE stays in a cell more than 4095 seconds, this IE is set to 4095.

rangeBoundList.explanation:
Maximum no. of cells of UE moving trajectory. Value
  is 16.

definitionList.name: Expected UE Activity Behaviour
descriptionList:
This IE indicates information about the expected
"UE activity behaviour" of the UE or the PDU session as defined in TS
23.501 [9].

elementList.name: Expected Activity Period
elementList.description: If set to "181" the expected activity time is longer than 180 seconds. The remaining values indicate the expected activity time in [seconds].

elementList.name: Expected Idle Period
elementList.description: If set to "181" the expected idle time is longer than 180 seconds. The remaining values indicate the expected idle time in [seconds].

elementList.name: Source of UE Activity Behaviour Information
elementList.description: If "subscription information" is indicated, the information contained in the Expected Activity Period IE and the Expected Idle Period IE, if present, is derived from subscription information. If "statistics" is indicated, the information contained in the Expected Activity Period IE and the Expected Idle Period IE, if present, is derived from statistical information.

definitionList.name: UE History Information
descriptionList:
This IE contains information about cells
that a UE has been served by in active state prior to the target cell.

elementList.name: Last Visited Cell Item
elementList.description: Most recent information is added to the top of this list.

rangeBoundList.explanation:
Maximum no. of cells in the UE history information.
  Value is 16.

definitionList.name: Last Visited Cell Information
descriptionList: This IE may contain cell specific information.

elementList.name: Last Visited E-UTRAN Cell Information
elementList.description: Defined in TS 36.413 [16].

elementList.name: Last Visited UTRAN Cell Information
elementList.description: Defined in TS 25.413 [28].

elementList.name: Last Visited GERAN Cell Information
elementList.description: Defined in TS 36.413 [16].

definitionList.name: Last Visited NG-RAN Cell Information
descriptionList:
This IE contains information about a cell.
In case of NR cell, this IE contains information about a set of NR cells with the
same NR ARFCN for reference point A, and the Global Cell ID IE
identifies one of the NR cells in the set. The information is to be used for RRM
purposes.

elementList.name: Time UE Stayed in Cell
elementList.description: The duration of time the UE stayed in the cell, or set of NR cells with the same NR ARFCN for reference point A, in seconds. If the duration is more than 4095s, this IE is set to 4095.

elementList.name: Time UE Stayed in Cell Enhanced Granularity
elementList.description: The duration of time the UE stayed in the cell, or set of NR cells with the same NR ARFCN for reference point A, in 1/10 seconds. If the duration is more than 4095s, this IE is set to 40950.

elementList.name: HO Cause Value
elementList.description: The cause for the handover.

definitionList.name: Cell Type
descriptionList: This IE provides the cell coverage area.

definitionList.name: Associated QoS Flow List
descriptionList:
This IE
indicates the list of QoS flows associated with e.g. a
DRB or UP TNL endpoint.

elementList.name: Current QoS Parameters Set Index
elementList.description: Index to the currently fulfilled alternative QoS parameters set

rangeBoundList.explanation:
Maximum no. of QoS flows allowed within one
  PDU session. Value is 64.

definitionList.name: Information on Recommended Cells and RAN Nodes for Paging
descriptionList:
This IE provides information on recommended
cells and NG-RAN nodes for paging.

definitionList.name: Recommended RAN Nodes for Paging
descriptionList:
This IE contains recommended NG-RAN nodes
for paging.

elementList.name: Recommended RAN Node Item
elementList.description: Includes visited and non-visited NG-RAN nodes, where visited NG-RAN nodes are listed in the order the UE visited them with the most recent NG-RAN node being the first in the list. Non-visited NG-RAN nodes are included after the visited NG-RAN node they are associated with.

elementList.name: CHOICE AMF Paging Target
elementList.description: The AMF paging target is either an NG-RAN node identity or a TAI as specified in TS 38.300 [8].

rangeBoundList.explanation:
Maximum no. of recommended
  NG-RAN nodes. Value is 16.

definitionList.name: PDU Session Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate
descriptionList:
This IE is applicable for all Non-GBR QoS
flows per PDU session which is defined for the downlink and the uplink direction
and is provided by the SMF to the NG-RAN node.

elementList.name: PDU Session Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate
elementList.description: Applicable for Non-GBR QoS flows.

elementList.name: PDU Session Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate Downlink
elementList.description: Indicates the PDU session Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate as specified in TS 23.501 [9] in the downlink direction.

elementList.name: PDU Session Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate Uplink
elementList.description: Indicates the PDU session Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate as specified in TS 23.501 [9] in the uplink direction.

definitionList.name: Maximum Integrity Protected Data Rate
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the
maximum aggregate data rate for integrity protected DRBs for a UE as defined in
TS 38.300 [8].

elementList.name: Maximum Integrity Protected Data Rate
elementList.description: Defines the upper bound of the aggregate data rate of user plane integrity protected data for either UL or DL.

definitionList.name: Overload Response
descriptionList: This IE indicates the required behaviour of the NG-RAN node in an overload situation.

definitionList.name: Overload Action
descriptionList:
This IE indicates which signalling traffic is subject to rejection by the NG-RAN node in
an AMF overload situation as
defined in TS 23.501 [9].

elementList.name: Overload Action
elementList.type: ENUMERATED (Reject RRC connection establishments for non-emergency MO DT, Reject RRC connection establishments for Signalling, Permit Emergency Sessions and mobile terminated services only, Permit High Priority Sessions and mobile terminated services only, )

definitionList.name: Traffic Load Reduction Indication
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the percentage of the type of traffic relative to the instantaneous
incoming rate at the NG-RAN node, as indicated in the Overload Action
IE, to be rejected.

definitionList.name: Slice Overload List
descriptionList: This IE indicates the list of overloaded slices.

rangeBoundList.explanation:
Maximum no. of signalled slice support items. Value
  is 1024.

definitionList.name: RAN Status Transfer Transparent Container
descriptionList:
This IE is produced by the source NG-RAN node
and is transmitted to the target NG-RAN node. It is used for intra 5GC NG
handover.
This IE is transparent to the AMF.

elementList.name: DRBs Subject to Status Transfer List
DRBs Subject to Status Transfer Item
UL COUNT Value
elementList.reference: COUNT Value for PDCP SN Length 12 9.3.1.109
elementList.description: PDCP-SN and HFN of the first missing UL PDCP SDU in case of 12 bit long PDCP-SN.

elementList.name: Receive Status of UL PDCP SDUs
elementList.description: The IE is used in case of 12 bit long PDCP-SN. The first bit indicates the status of the SDU after the First Missing UL PDCP SDU. The Nth bit indicates the status of the UL PDCP SDU in position (N + First Missing SDU Number) modulo (1 + the maximum value of the PDCP-SN). 0: PDCP SDU has not been received. 1: PDCP SDU has been received correctly.

elementList.name: UL COUNT Value
elementList.reference: COUNT Value for PDCP SN Length 18 9.3.1.110
elementList.description: PDCP-SN and HFN of the first missing UL PDCP SDU in case of 18 bit long PDCP-SN.

elementList.name: Receive Status of UL PDCP SDUs
elementList.description: The IE is used in case of 18 bit long PDCP-SN. The first bit indicates the status of the SDU after the First Missing UL PDCP SDU. The Nth bit indicates the status of the UL PDCP SDU in position (N + First Missing SDU Number) modulo (1 + the maximum value of the PDCP-SN). 0: PDCP SDU has not been received. 1: PDCP SDU has been received correctly.

elementList.name: DL COUNT Value
elementList.reference: COUNT Value for PDCP SN Length 12 9.3.1.109
elementList.description: PDCP-SN and HFN that the target NG-RAN node should assign for the next DL PDCP SDU not having an SN yet in case of 12 bit long PDCP-SN.

elementList.name: DL COUNT Value
elementList.reference: COUNT Value for PDCP SN Length 18 9.3.1.110
elementList.description: PDCP-SN and HFN that the target NG-RAN node should assign for the next DL PDCP SDU not having an SN yet in case of 18 bit long PDCP-SN.

elementList.name: Old Associated QoS Flow List - UL End Marker Expected
elementList.description: Indicates that the source NG-RAN node has initiated QoS flow re-mapping and has not yet received SDAP end markers, as described in TS 38.300 [8].

rangeBoundList.explanation:
Maximum no. of DRBs allowed towards one UE.
  Value is 32.

definitionList.name: COUNT Value for PDCP SN Length 12
descriptionList:
This IE contains a PDCP sequence number and
a hyper frame number in case of 12 bit long PDCP-SN.

definitionList.name: COUNT Value for PDCP SN Length 18
descriptionList:
This IE contains a PDCP sequence number and
a hyper frame number in case of 18 bit long PDCP-SN.

definitionList.name: RRC Establishment Cause
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the reason for RRC Connection Establishment as received from the UE
in the EstablishmentCause defined in TS 38.331 [18] and TS 36.331 [21],
or the reason for RRC Connection Resume as received from the UE in the ResumeCause
defined in TS 38.331 [18] and TS 36.331 [21], or the reason for RRC Connection
Establishment as received from the UE in the EstablishmentCause-NB defined
in TS 36.331 [21].

elementList.name: RRC Establishment Cause
elementList.type: ENUMERATED (emergency, highPriorityAccess, mt-Access, mo-Signalling, mo-Data, mo-VoiceCall, mo-VideoCall, mo-SMS, mps-PriorityAccess, mcs-PriorityAccess, , notAvailable, mo-ExceptionData)
elementList.description: The notAvailable value is used in case the UE is re-establishing an RRC connection but there is fallback to RRC connection establishment as described in [18], or the ResumceCause received from the UE does not map to any other value of the RRC Establishment Cause IE.

definitionList.name: Warning Area Coordinates
descriptionList:
This IE contains the affected alert area coordinates
of a warning message, and will be broadcast over the radio interface.

definitionList.name: Network Instance
descriptionList:
This IE provides the network instance to be
used by the NG-RAN node when selecting a particular transport network resource as
described in TS 23.501 [9].

definitionList.name: Secondary RAT Usage Information
descriptionList:
This IE provides information
on the secondary resources used with MR-DC.

rangeBoundList.explanation:
Maximum no.
  of QoS flows allowed within one PDU session. Value is 64.

definitionList.name: Volume Timed Report List
descriptionList:
This IE provides information
on the data usage.

elementList.name: Start Timestamp
elementList.description: UTC time encoded in the same format as the first four octets of the 64-bit timestamp format as defined in section 6 of IETF RFC 5905 [14]. It indicates the start time of the collecting period of the included Usage Count UL IE and Usage Count DL IE.

elementList.name: End Timestamp
elementList.description: UTC time encoded in the same format as the first four octets of the 64-bit timestamp format as defined in section 6 of IETF RFC 5905 [14]. It indicates the end time of the collecting period of the included Usage Count UL IE and Usage Count DL IE.

elementList.name: Usage Count UL
elementList.description: The unit is: octets.

elementList.name: Usage Count DL
elementList.description: The unit is: octets.

rangeBoundList.explanation:
Maximum no. of time reporting periods. Value is
  2.

definitionList.name: Redirection for Voice EPS Fallback
descriptionList:
This IE is used to indicate that the AMF and
the UE support the redirection for voice for EPS Fallback.

definitionList.name: UE Retention Information
descriptionList:
This IE allows the NG-RAN node and the AMF
to indicate whether prior UE related contexts and related UE-associated logical
NG-connections and RRC connections are intended to be retained.

definitionList.name: UL Forwarding
descriptionList:
This IE indicates that the QoS flow is proposed for forwarding of uplink
packets.

definitionList.name: CN Assisted RAN Parameters Tuning
descriptionList:
This IE provides information for assisting
in parameters tuning of the NG-RAN node.

elementList.name: Expected UE Behaviour
elementList.description: This IE may be present in case the Core Network Assistance Information for RRC INACTIVE IE is not included and is ignored otherwise.

definitionList.name: Common Network Instance
descriptionList:
This IE provides the common network instance
to be used by the NG-RAN node when selecting a particular transport network resource
as described in TS 23.501 [9] in a format common with 5GC.

definitionList.name: Data Forwarding Response E-RAB List
descriptionList:
This IE is used at inter-system HO to
provide DL data forwarding address information, if direct data forwarding is
applied.

rangeBoundList.explanation: Maximum no. of E-RABs. Value is 256.

definitionList.name: gNB Set ID
descriptionList:
The gNB Set
ID IE is used to identify a group of gNBs which transmit the same RIM-RS.

definitionList.name: RNC-ID
descriptionList: The RNC-ID is used to identify an RNC.

definitionList.name: Extended RNC-ID
descriptionList: This IE is used to identify an RNC.

elementList.name: Extended RNC-ID
elementList.description: This IE is used if the RNC identity has a value larger than 4095.

definitionList.name: RAT Information
descriptionList:
This IE provides RAT
related information associated with a TAC, used as described in TS 23.501 [9].

definitionList.name: Extended RAT Restriction Information
descriptionList:
This IE provides RAT
restrictions as specified in TS 23.501 [9].

elementList.name: Primary RAT Restriction
elementList.description: Each position in the bitmap represents a Primary RAT. If a bit is set to "1", the respective RAT is restricted for the UE. If a bit is set to "0", the respective RAT is not restricted for the UE. Bits 3-7 reserved for future use. The Primary RAT is the RAT used in the access cell, or target cell.

elementList.name: Secondary RAT Restriction
elementList.type: BIT STRING { e-UTRA (0), nR (1), e-UTRA-unlicensed (2), nR-unlicensed (3)} (SIZE(8, ))
elementList.description: Each position in the bitmap represents a Secondary RAT. If a bit is set to "1", the respective RAT is restricted for the UE. If a bit is set to "0", the respective RAT is not restricted for the UE. Bits 4-7 reserved for future use. A Secondary RAT is a RAT, distinct from the UE s primary RAT, used in any cell serving the UE excluding the PCell.

definitionList.name: SgNB UE X2AP ID
descriptionList: This IE uniquely identifies an UE over the X2 interface within an en-gNB.
The usage of this IE is defined in TS 37.340 [32].

definitionList.name: SRVCC Operation Possible
descriptionList:
This IE indicates that both UE and AMF are SRVCC-capable. NG-RAN
behaviour on receipt of this IE is specified in TS 23.216 [31].

elementList.name: SRVCC Operation Possible
elementList.description: The value "Possible" indicates that UE and AMF are SRVCC capable.

definitionList.name: IAB Authorized
descriptionList:
This IE provides information about the authorization
status of the IAB node.

elementList.name: IAB Authorized
elementList.description: Indicates the IAB node authorization status.

definitionList.name: TSC Traffic Characteristics
descriptionList:
This IE provides the traffic characteristics
of TSC QoS flows.

definitionList.name: TSC Assistance Information
descriptionList:
This IE provides the TSC assistance information
for a TSC QoS flow in the uplink or downlink (see TS 23.501 [9]).

definitionList.name: Periodicity
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the Periodicity of the TSC
QoS flow as defined in TS 23.501 [9].

elementList.name: Periodicity
elementList.description: Periodicity expressed in units of 1 us.

definitionList.name: Burst Arrival Time
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the Burst Arrival Time of
the TSC QoS flow as defined in TS 23.501 [9].

elementList.name: Burst Arrival Time
elementList.description: Encoded in the same format as the ReferenceTime IE as defined in TS 38.331 [18]. The value is truncated to 1 us granularity.

definitionList.name: Redundant QoS Flow Indicator
descriptionList:
This IE provides the redundant QoS flow indicator
for a QoS flow as specified in TS 23.051 [9].

elementList.name: Redundant QoS Flow Indicator
elementList.description: This IE indicates whether this QoS flow is requested for the redundant transmission. Value true indicates that redundant transmission is requested for this QoS flow. Value false indicates that redundant transmission is requested to be stopped if started.

definitionList.name: Extended Packet Delay Budget
descriptionList: This IE indicates the Packet Delay Budget for a QoS flow.

elementList.name: Extended Packet Delay Budget
elementList.description: Upper bound value for the delay that a packet may experience expressed in unit of 0.01ms.

definitionList.name: Redundant PDU Session Information
descriptionList:
This IE defines
Redundancy information to be
applied to a PDU session.

definitionList.name: NB-IoT Default Paging DRX
descriptionList: This IE indicates the NB-IoT Default Paging DRX as defined in TS 36.304 [29].

elementList.name: NB-IoT Default Paging DRX
elementList.description: Unit: [number of radioframes]

definitionList.name: NB-IoT Paging eDRX Information
descriptionList: This IE indicates the NB-IoT Paging eDRX parameters as defined in TS 36.304 [29].

elementList.name: NB-IoT Paging eDRX Cycle
elementList.type: ENUMERATED (hf2, hf4, hf6, hf8, hf10, hf12, hf14, hf16, hf32, hf64, hf128, hf256, hf512, hf1024, )
elementList.description: TeDRX defined in TS 36.304 [29]. Unit: [number of hyperframes].

elementList.name: NB-IoT Paging Time Window
elementList.description: Unit: [2.56 seconds]

definitionList.name: NB-IoT Paging DRX
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the NB-IoT UE specific Paging
DRX as defined in TS 36.304 [29].

elementList.name: NB-IoT Paging DRX
elementList.description: Unit: [number of radioframes]

definitionList.name: Enhanced Coverage Restriction
descriptionList:
This IE provides information
on the restriction information of using Coverage Enhancement.

elementList.name: Enhanced Coverage Restriction
elementList.description: Indicates whether the UE is restricted to use coverage enhancement. Value restricted indicates that the UE is not allowed to use coverage enhancement.

definitionList.name: Paging Assistance Data for CE Capable UE
descriptionList: This IE provides Assistance Data for paging CE capable UE.

elementList.name: Coverage Enhancement Level
elementList.description: Includes either the UEPagingCoverageInformation message as defined in 10.2.2 of TS 36.331 [21], or the UEPagingCoverageInformation-NB message as defined in 10.6.2 of TS 36.331 [21].

definitionList.name: UE Radio Capability ID
descriptionList: This IE contains the UE Radio Capability ID.

elementList.name: UE Radio Capability ID
elementList.description: Defined in 23.003 [23].

definitionList.name: WUS Assistance Information
descriptionList:
This IE provides WUS Assistance Information to be used by the NG-RAN
node for determining the WUS group for the UE.

elementList.name: Paging Probability Information
elementList.description: Unit: percentage

definitionList.name: UE Differentiation Information
descriptionList:
This IE is generated by the AMF based on the
UE subscription information, it provides the Expected UE Behavior Information.

elementList.name: Periodic Communication Indicator
elementList.description: This IE indicates whether the UE communicates periodically or not, e.g. only on demand.

elementList.name: Periodic Time
elementList.description: This IE indicates the interval time of periodic communication, the unit is: second

elementList.name: Scheduled Communication Time
elementList.description: This IE indicates the time zone and day of the week when the UE is available for communication.

elementList.name: Day of Week
elementList.description: Each position in the bitmap represents a day of the week: first bit = Mon, second bit =Tue, third bit =Wed, and so on. Value 1 indicates scheduled. Value 0 indicates not scheduled . If Day-Of-Week is not provided, this is interpreted as every day of the week.

elementList.name: Time of Day Start
elementList.description: This IE indicates the time to start of the day, each value represents the corresponding second since 00:00 of the day. If Time-Of-Day-Start is not provided, starting time is start of the day(s) indicated by Day-Of-Week-Mask.

elementList.name: Time of Day End
elementList.description: This IE indicates the time to start of the day, each value represents the corresponding second since 00:00 of the day. The value of this IE should be bigger than the value of Time of Day Start IE. If Time-Of-Day-End is not provided, ending time is end of the day(s) indicated by Day-Of-Week-Mask.

elementList.name: Traffic Profile
elementList.type: ENUMERATED (single packet, dual packets, multiple packets, )
elementList.description: single packet indicates single packet transmission (UL or DL), dual packets indicates dual packet transmission (UL with subsequent DL, or DL with subsequent UL), multiple packets indicates multiple packets transmission.

elementList.name: Battery Indication
elementList.type: ENUMERATED (battery powered, battery powered not rechargeable or replaceable, not battery powered, )
elementList.description: battery powered indicates that the UE is battery powered and the battery is rechargeable/replaceable, battery powered not rechargeable or replaceable indicates that the UE is battery powered but the battery is not rechargeable/replaceable, not battery powered indicates that the UE is not battery powered.

definitionList.name: NB-IoT UE Priority
descriptionList:
This IE provides the NB-IoT UE Priority and
to be used by the NG-RAN to prioritise between UEs accessing via NB-IoT.

elementList.name: NB-IoT UE Priority
elementList.description: Lower value indicates higher priority.

definitionList.name: NR V2X Services Authorized
descriptionList:
This IE provides information
on the authorization status of the UE to use the NR sidelink
for V2X services.

elementList.name: Vehicle UE
elementList.description: Indicates whether the UE is authorized as Vehicle UE

elementList.name: Pedestrian UE
elementList.description: Indicates whether the UE is authorized as Pedestrian UE

definitionList.name: LTE V2X Services Authorized
descriptionList:
This IE provides information
on the authorization status of the UE to use the LTE sidelink
for V2X services.

elementList.name: Vehicle UE
elementList.description: Indicates whether the UE is authorized as Vehicle UE

elementList.name: Pedestrian UE
elementList.description: Indicates whether the UE is authorized as Pedestrian UE

definitionList.name: NR UE Sidelink Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate
descriptionList:
This IE provides information
on the Aggregate Maximum Bitrate of the UE s sidelink communication for NR V2X services.

elementList.name: NR UE Sidelink Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate
elementList.description: Value 0 is not valid, and considered as a logical error by the receiving NG-RAN node.

definitionList.name: LTE UE Sidelink Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate
descriptionList:
This IE provides information
on the Aggregate Maximum Bitrate of the UE s sidelink communication for LTE V2X services.

elementList.name: LTE UE Sidelink Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate
elementList.description: Value 0 is not valid, and considered as a logical error by the receiving NG-RAN node.

definitionList.name: PC5 QoS Parameters
descriptionList:
This IE provides information
on the PC5 QoS parameters of the UE s sidelink communication for NR PC5.

elementList.name: PQI
elementList.description: PQI is a special 5QI as specified in TS 23.501 [9].

elementList.name: PC5 Flow Bit Rates
elementList.description: Only applies for GBR QoS Flows.

elementList.name: Guaranteed Flow Bit Rate
elementList.description: Guaranteed Bit Rate for the PC5 QoS flow. Details in TS 23.501 [9].

elementList.name: Maximum Flow Bit Rate
elementList.description: Maximum Bit Rate for the PC5 QoS flow. Details in TS 23.501 [9].

elementList.name: Range
elementList.description: Only applies for groupcast.

elementList.name: PC5 Link Aggregate Bit Rates
elementList.description: Only applies for non-GBR QoS Flows.

rangeBoundList.explanation:
Maximum no. of PC5 QoS
  flows allowed towards one UE. Value is 2048.

definitionList.name: Alternative QoS Parameters Set List
descriptionList:
This IE contains alternative sets of QoS
parameters which the NG-RAN node can indicate to be fulfilled when notification
control is enabled and it cannot fulfil the requested list of QoS parameters.

rangeBoundList.explanation:
Maximum no. of alternative sets of QoS Parameters
  allowed for the QoS profile. Value is 8.

definitionList.name: Alternative QoS Parameters Set Index
descriptionList:
This IE indicates
the QoS parameters set which can currently be fulfilled.

elementList.name: Alternative QoS Parameters Set Index
elementList.description: Indicates the index of the item within the the Alternative QoS Parameters Set List IE corresponding to the currently fulfilled alternative QoS parameters set.

definitionList.name: Alternative QoS Parameters Set Notify Index
descriptionList:
This IE indicates
the QoS parameters set which can currently be fulfilled.

elementList.name: Alternative QoS Parameters Set Notify Index
elementList.description: Indicates the index of the item within the the Alternative QoS Parameters Set List IE corresponding to the currently fulfilled alternative QoS parameters set. Value 0 indicates that NG-RAN cannot even fulfil the lowest alternative parameters set.

definitionList.name: Paging eDRX Information
descriptionList:
This IE indicates the Paging eDRX parameters
as defined in TS 36.304 [29].

elementList.name: Paging eDRX Cycle
elementList.type: ENUMERATED (hfhalf, hf1, hf2, hf4, hf6, hf8, hf10, hf12, hf14, hf16, hf32, hf64, hf128, hf256, )
elementList.description: TeDRX defined in TS 36.304 [29]. Unit: [number of hyperframes].

elementList.name: Paging Time Window
elementList.description: Unit: [1.28 second].

definitionList.name: CE-mode-B Restricted
descriptionList:
This IE provides information
on the restriction information of using Coverage Enhancement Mode B.

elementList.name: CE-mode-B Restricted
elementList.description: Indicates whether the UE is restricted to use coverage enhancement. Value restricted indicates that the UE is not allowed to use coverage enhancement mode B. Value not-restricted indicates that the UE is allowed to use coverage enhancement mode B.

definitionList.name: CE-mode-B Support Indicator
descriptionList:
This IE indicates
whether CE-mode-B as specified in TS 36.306[42] is supported for the UE.

definitionList.name: LTE-M Indication
descriptionList:
This IE is provided
by the NG-RAN node to inform that the UE indicates category M1 or M2 in its UE
Radio Capability.

definitionList.name: Suspend Request Indication
descriptionList:
This IE indicates that the NG-RAN node requests immediate transition
to RRC idle with suspend, as specified in TS 23.502 [10].

definitionList.name: Suspend Response Indication
descriptionList:
This IE is used by the AMF to inform the NG-RAN node to suspend the UE and send it to
RRC_IDLE, as specified in TS 23.502 [10].

definitionList.name: UE User Plane CIoT Support Indicator
descriptionList:
This IE indicates whether
User Plane CIoT 5GS Optimisation as specified in TS 23.501 [9] is supported
for the UE.

elementList.name: UE User Plane CIoT Support Indicator

definitionList.name: Global TNGF ID
descriptionList:
This IE is
used to globally identify a TNGF.

definitionList.name: Global W-AGF ID
descriptionList:
This IE is
used to globally identify a W-AGF.

definitionList.name: Global TWIF ID
descriptionList:
This IE is used
to globally identify a TWIF.

definitionList.name: W-AGF User Location Information
descriptionList:
This IE indicates
the location information via wireline access as specified in TS 23.316 [34].

elementList.name: Global Line ID
elementList.description: Encoded as defined in TS 23.003 [23].

elementList.name: HFC Node ID
elementList.description: Indicates the identifier of the HFC node as specified in [37]. Encoded as defined in TS 23.003 [23].

elementList.name: Global Cable ID
elementList.description: Encoded as defined in TS 23.003 [23].

definitionList.name: Global eNB ID
descriptionList:
This IE is
used to globally identify an eNB (see TS 36.401 [38]).

elementList.name: Macro eNB ID
elementList.description: Equal to the 20 leftmost bits of the Cell Identity IE contained in the E-UTRAN CGI IE (see TS 36.423 [40] subclause 9.3.1.9) of each cell served by the eNB.

elementList.name: Home eNB ID
elementList.description: Equal to the Cell Identity IE contained in the E-UTRAN CGI IE (see TS 36. 423 [40] subclause 9.3.1.9) of the cell served by the eNB.

elementList.name: Short Macro eNB ID
elementList.description: Equal to the 18 leftmost bits of the Cell Identity IE (see TS 36. 423 [40] subclause 9.3.1.9) of each cell served by the eNB.

elementList.name: Long Macro eNB ID
elementList.description: Equal to the 21 leftmost bits of the Cell Identity IE (see TS 36. 423 [40] subclause 9.3.1.9) of each cell served by the eNB.

definitionList.name: UE History Information from UE
descriptionList:
This IE contains information about mobility
history report for a UE.

elementList.name: CHOICE UE History Information from UE
NR Mobility History Report
elementList.description: VisitedCellInfoList contained in the UEInformationResponse message (TS 38.331 [18]).

definitionList.name: MDT Configuration
descriptionList: This IE defines the MDT configuration parameters.

definitionList.name: MDT PLMN List
descriptionList:
The purpose of the MDT PLMN List IE
is to provide the list of PLMN allowed for MDT.

rangeBoundList.explanation:
Maximum no. of PLMNs in the MDT PLMN list. Value
  is 16.

definitionList.name: MDT Configuration-NR
descriptionList:
This IE defines the MDT configuration
parameters of NR.

elementList.name: MDT Activation
elementList.type: ENUMERATED (Immediate MDT only, Logged MDT only, Immediate MDT and Trace, )

elementList.name: TAC
elementList.description: The TAI is derived using the current serving PLMN.

elementList.name: Measurements to Activate

First Bit = M1, Second Bit= M2, Third Bit = M4, Fourth Bit = M5, Fifth Bit = M6, Sixth Bit = M7, Seventh Bit = logging of M1 from event triggered measurement reports according to existing RRM configuration, other bits reserved for future use.
